<p style="FONT-STYLE: normal; MARGIN-TOP: 0pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-WEIGHT: normal" align="left"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 14pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">FROM THE EDITOR</span><br /></span><br /></p>
<p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">When was the last time you read a book report?&nbsp; Probably looking over one of your kids' homework assignments, right?&nbsp; Well, that's the lead story in this issue, courtesy of PIO-trainer and consultant Karen Terrill.</span></p>
<p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Then, Melissa Mack and Charlie McDonald from Crisis Management International bring us an interesting concept -- The Sincerity Bar -- and how you can clear it.</span></p>
<p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">If you want more than just the education offered by this ezine, please consider browsing the <a style="COLOR: #4c869c; TEXT-DECORATION: underline" track="on" shape="rect" href="http://bernsteincrisismanagement.blogspot.com/" linktype="link" target="_blank">Bernstein Crisis Management blog </a></span></p>
<p style="FONT-STYLE: normal; MARGIN-TOP: 0pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-WEIGHT: normal" align="left"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">I manage with my son Erik and the <a style="COLOR: #4c869c; TEXT-DECORATION: underline" track="on" shape="rect" href="http://managementhelp.org/blogs/crisis-management/" linktype="link" mce_shape="rect" mce_href="http://managementhelp.org/blogs/crisis-management" target="_blank">Crisis Management blog</a> I host over at Carter McNamara's Free Management Library.<br /></span></p>
<p style="FONT-STYLE: normal; MARGIN-TOP: 0pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-WEIGHT: normal" align="left"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><br /></span></p>
<p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">As always, if you like what you see, please share it with others by using the "Forward Email" link at the bottom of the ezine and tell them to subscribe!&nbsp;<span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold"> IMPORTANT NOTE:</span> If you just "Forward" using your own email program's "Forward" function and your recipient thinks they're being spammed, they can click on the Opt Out link and opt YOU off the list.&nbsp;&nbsp; So use the "Forward Email" link, please.</span><br /></span></p>
<p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span>&nbsp;<br /></span></p>
